--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Window Object
The global object, the following are the methods of the global object
    setInterval
    setTimeout
    alert
    confirm
    prompt
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Document Object
This is the most important object of the DOM. It holds all the important methods
that we will use.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Nodes
Each element in the DOM is called a node.

Types of Nodes
    Document Fragment
    Element Node
    Attribute node
    Comment Node
    Text Node
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adding elements to the DOM
    element.appendChild(childNode)
    element.insertBefore(newNode)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Removing elements from the DOM
    element.removeChild(childNode)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DOM traversal
    element.parentNode
    element.childNodes
    element.children
    element.nextSibling
    element.previousSibling
    element.lastChild
    element.firstChild

    element.lastElementChild
    element.firstElementChild
    element.nextElementSibling
    element.previousElementSibling
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Replacing elements
    element.replaceChild(newChild, oldChild)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Cloning elements
    element.cloneNode(true)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Obtaining a reference of the DOM elements
    document.getElementsByTagName(tagname)
    document.getElementsById(id)
    document.getElementsByClassName(className)
    document.querySelector(selector)
    document.querySelectorAll(selector)

    Note: the nodelist returned by querySelector is not a live List
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STYLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adding styles to the element
Just assign the style to the style property of the element in question
    element.style.backgroundColor = white;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Obtaining the computed style of the element
    getComputedStyle(element, null).getPropertyValue("propertyName");
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EVENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DOM Level 0 events
They are volatile and are directly used by using the onevent property of the
element.
    element.onclick = someFunction;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Standard event model
    element.addEventListener("eventName", functionObject, false);
    element.removeEventListener("eventName", functionObject, false);

THe this keyword in the standard event model refers to the element on which the
event happened.
    this
    evt.target
    evt.preventDefault()
    evt.type

Legacy IE event model
    element.attachEvent("onclick", functionObject)l;
    element.detachEvent("onclick", functionObject)l;

Here "this" refers instead to the global object and we cannot make use of it.
Also we make use of the global event object which contains all the important
information
    that = event.srcElement
    event.type
    event.returnValue = false;

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Phases of events
Ther are three phases in any event actvity, 
    Capture: it is a traversal from the root of the DOM to the event that was
    clicked.

    Bubbling: it is a traversal from the element that was clicked to the root of
    the DOM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


